# mini.align — `gA{motion}<char>` pads each line in the motion's range with
# spaces before the first occurrence of `<char>` so they all line up.
# `gAip=` aligns a paragraph on `=`. `gAap=` is identical here since the
# paragraph has no trailing blank-line content.

write code.txt "let a = 1\nlet bb = 2\nlet ccc = 3\n"
open code.txt
command editor.use_vim

# Cursor at top. `gAip=` aligns the paragraph on `=`.
key g
key A
key i
key p
key =

# All three `=` should line up at the same column.
expect screen contains "let a   = 1"
expect screen contains "let bb  = 2"
expect screen contains "let ccc = 3"
